package com.beginnerdsa.step3._4_Greedy;
/*
at a party of penguins,
there are N number of male penguin and N number of female penguin
each male and female penguin wish to dance with the opposite gender penguin as per there preference
of their height, some male penguin want female penguin to be shorter than them and some wish there female penguin
should be taller than them, same with female penguins.

height of penguin is mentioned along with a sign in front of each height, either positive or negative,
telling that what type of partner do they want, of positive, then they want a penguin partner taller than them
if negative that means they want a partner shorter than them.
we need to print the number of maximum compatible couples that can be partners.


eg:input:  2 (no. of N)
          -1800 -2200 ( 2 male)
           1900  1800 (2 female)

           total max compatible is: 1
           either (-2200,1900) or (-2200,1800)


//bruteforce:


 */
import java.util.Scanner;
import java.util.HashMap;
import java.util.Map;

public class _07_dancing_penguins {
    public static void main(String [] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
//        int[] male=new int[n];
//        int[] female=new int[n];

        Map<Integer,Integer> male1=new HashMap<>();
        Map<Integer,Integer> female1=new HashMap<>();

        int lowerBound=-1;
        int answer=0;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
//            male[i]=sc.nextInt();
            int j=sc.nextInt();
            male1.put(j,male1.getOrDefault(j,0)+1);

        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
//            female[i]=sc.nextInt();
            int k=sc.nextInt();
            female1.put(k,female1.getOrDefault(k,0)+1);
        }
        int s= 0;
        for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> male: male1.entrySet()){
            int k=male.getKey();
            boolean b=false;
            for (Map.Entry<Integer, Integer> female : female1.entrySet()){
                if(k<0){
                     s=female.getKey();
                    if (female.getKey()>0 && female.getKey()<Math.abs(k)){
                        int a=Math.abs(k-female.getKey());
                        if(lowerBound>a){
                            lowerBound=a;
                            b=true;
                        }
                    }
                }
                if (k>0){
                    s=female.getKey();
                    if (female.getKey()<0 && Math.abs(female.getKey())>k){
                        int a=Math.abs(female.getKey()-k);
                        if(lowerBound>a){
                            lowerBound=a;
                            b=true;
                        }
                    }

                }
            }
            if (b){
                answer++;
                female1.put(s,female1.get(s)-1);
                male1.put(k,male1.get(k)-1);

            }

        }
        System.out.println(answer);

    }
}


//optimized

/*
in this we will make 4 different arrays: 2 for male and 2 for females, 1 male array will include all males that require female height greater than them
and another array where males requires females of less height than them.
same with female array

then we will sort the array so that we can iterate them easily using 2 pointer.
MALES: 5, 10, 15 ,-5 , -10 , -15, -25
FEMALES: 5 ,10 ,15, -5, -10, -15, -21

We will make 4 arrays respectively and sort them:

P1M:5, 10, 15
P2M: -5 , -10 , -15, -25

P1F:5 ,10 ,15
P2F:-5, -10, -15, -21

now all males that are positive requires females that are greater than them so surely they will require those females that want males to be shorter than them.
so P1M will make pairs with only P2F
and similarly P2M will make pair with P1F

now,
we will keep 1 pointer to P2M and another pointer to P1F and will check if they make pair if yes then we shift both pointer 1 step ahead
if no then we shift male pointer ahead.
and eventually count the pairs.

same with P1M and P2F but here if pair does not makes then we shift female pointer otherwise we shift both pointers.


*/


